Many other libraries use 4.1, including Google's `Geolocation`:

```ts
// Type definitions for Google Geolocation 0.4.8
// Project: https://code.google.com/p/geo-location-javascript/
// Definitions by: Vincent Bortone <https://github.com/vbortone>
// Definitions: https://github.com/DefinitelyTyped/DefinitelyTyped
// Minimum TypeScript Version: 4.1
```

@amcasey The new type features will help simplify the type definitions a whole bunch, I used some of the newer features of typescript to make this type definition

For example, in tailwind, they have complex types such as:

```ts
export type TailwindStandardNegativeSpacing = {
    [key in keyof TailwindStandardSpacing as `-${key}`]: string;
};
```

This type is an exact replica of a type, except it has a `-` sign in front of all values. This feature is in new versions of TypeScript.

